{"questionId":"2806027","questionHtml":"<p>Calculate the distance between <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">P</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>equating their<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> to their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>L</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> (or equivalent)&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>valid attempt to solve their quadratic&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><mi>x</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept both solutions <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> here, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn></math> may be seen in working to find coordinates of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi></math> or distance.</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>substituting their value of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math> (not <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>) into their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>f</mi><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>)</mo></math> or their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">L</mi></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn></math>&nbsp; OR&nbsp;&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mn>1</mn><mn>4</mn></mfrac><msup><mfenced><mrow><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Q</mi><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>,</mo><mo> </mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo></math>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>correct substitution into distance formula&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <em><strong>(A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msqrt><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>-</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mo>(</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>-</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>4</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></msqrt></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>distance</mi><mo>=</mo><